<dl id="n51146f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n51" href="#n51146f">N51 (VI.B.44)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n51all.htm#n51146f"> 146(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Master of Revels</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The first theatre in Dublin was in Werburgh Street, somewhere between Hoey&apos;s Court and Ship Street, and was erected by John Ogilby, a Scotchman, who was Deputy <mark>Master of the Revels</mark> under the Earl of Strafford. Its period was 1635-1641. <small> Rev. S.C. Hughes, <a name="PVDD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#PVDD"><cite title="source">The Pre-Victorian Drama in Dublin</cite></a> (1904) 2</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
